Dax Measures 9

Create the following DAX Measures 

1.  Total Violation

         Total Violation = CALCULATE (COUNT ('Traffic Violation'[Date Of Stop]))

2.   Violation Per Month

               Violation Per Month = DIVIDE (([Total Violation]),DISTINCTCOUNT('Date'[YearMonthShort]),0) + 0

3.  Total State In and Out violation

             Total State in and Out = CALCULATE (COUNT ('Traffic Violation'[Out State]))

4.   Violation Per Month LY

             Violation Per Month LY = CALCULATE ([Violation Per Month], DATEADD('Date'[Date], -1,YEAR))

5.   YOY

             YOY = DIVIDE([Violation Per Month] - [Violation Per Month LY],[Violation Per Month LY],0)

6.   Out State of Violation

         Out State Violation = DIVIDE(CALCULATE('Traffic Violation'[Total State in and Out],FILTER('Traffic Violation’,‘Traffic Violation'[Out State] = 1)),[Total State in and Out],0)


7.   Indicator YOY

         Indicator YOY = If([YOY]<0,UNICHAR(9660),UNICHAR(9650))



 8.   Last Refreshed Date 

            First Click on transform Data icon in the Home Ribbon of Power BI Desktop

           Then click on New Source  ------>  Blank Query

           Then write the bottom query and rename the created column to Last Refreshed Date           

           Then click on convert to table button on the ribbon


                               

               Loaded Table 

                                


                Then Drag Visual Card from Visualizations  and drop Last Date  Refreshed  from created table  

                           

This link helps how we can create last date the data refreshed
